gameRecap.title: Game Recap: 76ers 104, Cavaliers 97
gameRecap.excerpt: The 76ers defeated the Cavaliers, 104-97, to snap a two-game skid and improved to 33-23 on the year. Tyrese Maxey led the 76ers with 24 points, seven rebounds, and five assists as Cam Payne (16 points) and Tobias Harris (15 points, nine rebounds) totaled 31 points. Jarrett Allen led Cleveland with 24 points and nine rebounds as Darius Garland added 20 points, nine assists, and five rebounds. The Cavaliers moved to 36-19 on the year.
